# Slate Builder — environment configuration (engine-only branch, no LLM).
#
# Copy the vars you need into .env.local for local dev. On Vercel, set them in
# Project Settings → Environment Variables. Values shown are CODE defaults — you
# only need to set a var to override its default (or for the secrets, which have
# no default).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vercel deploy — required
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN - Vercel Blob RW token. Backs the durable lines/odds
#   snapshots (api/_lib/blob-store.js via @vercel/blob). AUTO-INJECTED by Vercel
#   when a Blob store is connected to the project — prefer the injected value over
#   setting it by hand. Needed locally so refresh scripts can write. Reads fall
#   back to the bundled data/*.json snapshot when the blob is empty/unreachable.

# REFRESH_TOKEN - server only — bearer token required by POST /api/refresh-lines.
# VITE_REFRESH_TOKEN - client-bundled — MUST equal REFRESH_TOKEN. Powers the
#   "REFRESH LINES" button (src/App.jsx). Vite exposes any VITE_*-prefixed var to
#   the frontend bundle, so set it in .env.local for dev and on Vercel for BOTH
#   Production + Preview. Bundle exposure is acceptable: the endpoint is
#   rate-limited (6/60s) and this is a single-user tool.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vercel deploy — optional
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Verdict telemetry (Axiom). If unset, logging is silently skipped.
# AXIOM_TOKEN   - Axiom ingest token.
# AXIOM_DATASET - dataset name (default: "props_verdict").

# CRON_SECRET - bearer required by GET /api/refresh-lines (the Vercel cron path).
#   Only needed if a cron is configured (none in vercel.json today).

# Stats fallback (NBA/WNBA) — balldontlie.io fallback for stats.nba.com.
# BALLDONTLIE_API_KEY - server only.

# Tuning knobs (all have code defaults; override only if needed):
# MAX_LINES_PER_PLAYER    - cap on lines analyzed per /api/analyze-all (default: 60)
# RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS    - /api/analyze rate-limit window in ms (default: 60000)
# RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS - max /api/analyze requests per window per IP (default: 10)
# NODE_ENV                - development | production | test (affects error detail)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Home bridge — residential-IP refresh (PrizePicks blocks cloud IPs)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed if you run the home-bridge refresh path (scripts/refresh-bridge.mjs).

# HOME_REFRESH_URL   - Vercel only — public HTTPS URL of the home bridge. When set,
#   the deployed /api/refresh-lines forwards refresh clicks here after its own
#   cloud-IP scrape returns 0 props.
# HOME_BRIDGE_SECRET - shared by Vercel + the home machine — bearer the Vercel
#   function sends and refresh-bridge.mjs validates. Generate: openssl rand -hex 32.
# HOME_BRIDGE_PORT   - home machine only — port the bridge listens on (default: 4000).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Scripts only (not used by the deployed app)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WATCHDOG_PING_URL    - funnel-watchdog.mjs probe target (default: the prod
#                        /api/refresh-lines?ping=1 URL).
# ENTRIES_URL_PATTERN  - regex to recognize the PrizePicks entries endpoint in
#                        fetch-prizepicks-entries.mjs (default: "entries").

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Auto-managed by Vercel — DO NOT set by hand
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN - short-lived; injected by Vercel / `vercel env pull`.
